(also an inconsistently-implemented change from classic )296 788 MS
(iostreams.)1153 788 MS
(The state variable "frozen" means that the stream buffer is fixed and cannot be changed. Various operations that set)296 878 MS
(or depend on "frozen" assume the "freeze" operation by default sets "frozen", as the name of the function implies. The)296 923 MS
(description of "freeze" says the default operation is to clear "frozen" \(inconsistent with its use\), and that a "false")296 968 MS
(argument to "freeze" sets "frozen" \(inconsistent with the name of the function\). If the description of "freeze" is)296 1013 MS
(reversed, it then corresponds to classic )296 1058 MS
(iostream behavior, and becomes consistent with its use throughout section)895 1058 MS
(D.7. But wait -- there's more.)296 1103 MS
(In classic )296 1193 MS
(iostreams, the freeze function had an )447 1193 MS
(int parameter. The function now appears in three versions in three)1018 1193 MS
(subsections of D.7. In D.7.1 it has a )296 1238 MS
(bool parameter, but with a default argument value of 1 instead of "true".  In)852 1238 MS
(D.7.3 and D.7.4 it has an )296 1283 MS
(int parameter \(with a default value of 1\).)690 1283 MS
(By changing the one instance of a )296 1373 MS
(bool parameter type back to )818 1373 MS
(int, and by reversing the sense of the description of)1251 1373 MS
("freeze", the draft will become internally consistent, and will correspond to classic )296 1418 MS
(iostreams.)1563 1418 MS
(The other possibility is to leave this freeze's parameter type )296 1508 MS
(bool, change its default value to "true", and change the)1211 1508 MS
(other two instances of "freeze" to )296 1553 MS
(bool with default "true" as well.)811 1553 MS
(I suggest the changes above as being the minimum needed change, and because it corresponds to classic )296 1643 MS
(iostreams. If)1890 1643 MS
(someone thinks the larger change \(making everything )296 1688 MS
(bool\) is appropriate, I have no objection, particularly if some)1121 1688 MS
(implementations currently use )296 1733 MS
(bool.)767 1733 MS
([)296 1823 MS
(pjp]  Microsoft VC++ has defined the parameter to freeze as type )308 1823 MS
(bool since V4.2 was released in July 1996. It does)1313 1823 MS
(so because the committee once voted to change )296 1868 MS
(int to )1023 1868 MS
(bool. I'm away from my office, so I can't cite chapter and verse)1113 1868 MS
(as is my wont, but I'm comfortable that this is the case.)296 1913 MS
(Thus, I believe the proper fix is to consider this an incomplete edit that needs to be completed to satisfy the stated)296 2003 MS
(will of the committee. It also aligns the draft with an existing practice that we encouraged with an earlier vote.)296 2048 MS
